@TITLE "MMUINFO(1)ĀmanualĀpage"
 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name mmuinfo - Gives information about module @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}mmuinfo@{"ub"} [@{"i"}generaloptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}queryoption@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}otheroptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}] @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description @{"b"}mmuinfo@{"ub"} loads module from @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"} (or module from standard input if no @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"} is given) and prints meta information about module to standard output. If no @{"i"}query option@{"ui"} is given, then @{"b"}mmuinfo@{"ub"} will print following information (if available): module file name, song title, song time, module type, number of channels, number of positions, number of patterns, number of instruments, number of samples, song comment. If @{"i"}query option@{"ui"} is given, then information that will be printed depend of this option. Only one @{"i"}query option@{"ui"} can be given at once. 

@{"b"}mmuinfo@{"ub"} is part of the MikMod Utilities package, and uses MikMod Sound Library to load modules. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Exit Status @{"b"}mmuplay@{"ub"} uses standard exit status, as defined in sysexits.h. See a description of all exit codes in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}General Options See a description of all general options in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}Query Options @{"b"}-i, --title@{"ub"} Print module title (song name). @{"b"}-t, --time@{"ub"} Print song time (seconds). @{"b"}-y, --type@{"ub"} Print module type (which tracker format). @{"b"}-n, --numchn@{"ub"} Print number of channels in the module. @{"b"}-p, --numpos@{"ub"} Print number of positions in the module. @{"b"}-e, --numpat@{"ub"} Print number of patterns in the module. @{"b"}-m, --numins@{"ub"} Print number of instruments in the module. @{"b"}-a, --numsmp@{"ub"} Print number of samples in the module. @{"b"}-u, --instruments@{"ub"} List all instruments in the module. This will print table, the first column shows the instrument number, the second column shows the instrument name. @{"b"}-s, --samples@{"ub"} List all samples in the module. This will print table, the first column contains sample numbers, the second column shows the sample width (8 or 16 bit), the third column shows the number of audio channels (mono or stereo), the 4-th column contains the sample lengths (in samples), the 5-th column shows the sample name. Use @{" " link "'mmurip.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmurip@{"ub"}(1) to extract samples from the module. @{"b"}-c, --comment@{"ub"} Print module comment. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Other Options @{"b"}-l, --label=@{"ub"}@{"i"}LABEL@{"ui"} Print LABEL as filename for standard input. @{" " link "'#toc7'/MAIN"}Bugs Song time computation works slow. If you found other bugs, please let me known. @{" " link "'#toc8'/MAIN"}Author Konstantin Korikov <lostclus@ua.fm> @{" " link "'#toc9'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mikmod.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mikmod(1)@{"ub"} 


